# Avoid loadMissing Everywhere

Treat `loadMissing()` as a bad pattern across the codebase.

## Why

- It can hide implicit queries and cause N+1 issues when code runs in loops.
- It masks missing eager loading that should be explicit at the query boundary.

## What to do instead

Use relations directly (for example `$program->address`) and eager-load where records are fetched (`with()` in query builders, or explicit `load()` at orchestration boundaries).

With strict/lazy-loading protection enabled, direct relation access fails fast in development, making missing eager loads visible before shipping.

```php
// Bad
$model->loadMissing(['address']);

// Good
$model->address;
```
